#: ../../../reference/lists.md:1
msgid "Lists"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/lists.md:3
msgid ""
"Lists are useful because they emphasize certain information in regular text. "
"They can able be used to enumerate or provide an easier reference. Sphinx "
"allows for various forms of lists, each of which can be used in a different "
"manner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/lists.md:5
msgid "Bullet Lists"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/lists.md:10
msgid ""
"- Bullet lists in reStructuredText are fairly straightforward.\n"
"- A bunch of bullet points.\n"
"\n"
"  - Nested bullets should be indented by **exactly** two spaces.\n"
"  - They also need a blank line before and after them, otherwise it doesn't\n"
"    work right.\n"
"\n"
"- It is also possible to have multiple paragraphs in a bullet.\n"
"\n"
"  Make sure to have a blank line between the paragraphs, and to indent the\n"
"  paragraphs to the correct level."
msgstr ""

